'''Freeadvice''' is a free US legal information web service that was established in 1997. It has won extensive awards, including having been named by [[Forbes]] in 2000 as a "Best of the Web",<ref>{{cite web|last1=Newcomb|first1=Kelly|title=Legal Advice|url=https://www.forbes.com/forbes/2000/0522/6512128a.html|website=Forbes.com|publisher=Forbes Media LLC|accessdate=29 August 2016}}</ref> by [[PC World (magazine)|PC World]] in 2004, as one of the Best 125 Free Sites on the entire Web,<ref>{{cite web|last1=Willmott|first1=Don|title=50 from the Best of the Internet|url=https://www.pcmag.com/article2/0,2817,1516962,00.asp|website=PCMag.com|publisher=[[Ziff Davis, LLC]]|accessdate=29 August 2016}}</ref> as one of the 100 featured sites in [[PC Magazine]]’s Best 1000 websites, as the legal site of 2009 by [[Access Magazine]],<ref>{{cite web|title=FreeAdvice|url=http://familyfirst.com/freeadvice.html|website=Family First|publisher=Socrates Digital, LLC|accessdate=29 August 2016}}</ref> and to have received recognition in the [[New York Times]]<ref>{{cite web|last1=Lee|first1=Jennifer|title=Legal Aid Online; Web's Law Library: A Partial Catalog|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2001/02/22/technology/legal-aid-online-web-s-law-library-a-partial-catalog.html|website=The New York Times|publisher=The New York Times Company|accessdate=29 August 2016}}</ref> in 2001, [[Wall Street Journal]]<ref>{{cite web|last1=Schmittq|first1=Richard|title=A Growing Number of Sites Dispense Legal Advice Online|url=https://www.wsj.com/articles/SB933556084181501147|website=Wall Street Journal|publisher=Dow Jones & Company|accessdate=29 August 2016}}</ref> in 1999, and [[Washington Post]]’s reviews of legal websites in 1998.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Meng|first1=Nancie|title=Tax Time Links|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-srv/business/longterm/tax/links.htm|website=Washington Post|publisher=The Washington Post Company|accessdate=29 August 2016}}</ref>

Freeadvice is an affiliate of the [[Advice Company]] located in [[Sausalito, California]]<ref>{{cite web|title=About FreeAdvice.com|url=http://www.freeadvice.com/company/aboutus.htm|website=FreeAdvice.com|publisher=Advice Company|accessdate=29 August 2016}}</ref> and was founded by attorney Gerry Goldsholle.<ref>{{cite web|title=FreeAdvice.com Press Release|url=http://www.businesswire.com/news/home/20050322005942/en/Free-Living-Form-FreeAdvice.com|website=Business Wire|publisher=Business Wire|accessdate=29 August 2016}}</ref>

