{{italic title}} '''''Kolo''''' is a [[Croatia]]n literary magazine published by [[Matica hrvatska]].
==History and profile== The magazine was founded by [[Stanko Vraz]] in 1842. Matica hrvatska became its publisher in 1847. In 1851, the publishing of ''Kolo'' temporarily ceased (replaced by ''Neven'', which was in turn replaced by ''[[Vienac]]'').<ref>{{cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=-0mJ7blUGtQC&pg=PA42|page=42|title=History of the Literary Cultures of East-Central Europe: Junctures and Disjunctures in the 19th and 20th Centuries|volume=3|authors=Marcel Cornis-Pope, John Neubauer|publisher=John Benjamins Publishing|year=2004|isbn=9789027234551|accessdate=10 February 2013}}</ref>
The popular Bosnian poem, and later song, ''[[Emina (poem)|Emina]]'' by [[Aleksa Šantić]] was first published in ''Kolo'' in 1902.<ref>{{cite news|author=|url=http://www.dnevni-list.ba/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=10139:dobro-dola-kui-lijepa-emina&catid=7:kultura&Itemid=8|title=Dobro Doslo Kuci Lljepa Emina|newspaper=[[Dnevni list]]|date=28 May 2010|accessdate=28 December 2012}}</ref> [[File:Ernest Fišer na promociji Hrvatskog kajkavskog kolendara 24.11.2017..JPG|140px|thumb|Ernest Fišer]] Editors of ''Kolo'' have included [[Marijan Matković]], [[Joža Horvat]], [[Slavko Kolar]], [[Gustav Krklec]], [[Vjekoslav Kaleb]], [[Vlatko Pavletić]], [[Milivoj Slaviček]], [[Miroslav Vaupotić]], [[Igor Zidić]].<ref>{{cite journal|url = http://www.matica.hr/kolo/314/Proslov/|language=Croatian|journal=Kolo|issue=1|year=2009|title= Proslov|author= Ernest Fišer|accessdate=4 January 2013}}</ref>
