A '''legal periodical''' is a [[Periodical literature|periodical]] about [[law]]. Legal periodicals include legal newspapers, [[law review]]s, periodicals published by way of commerce, periodicals published by practitioner bodies, and periodicals concerned with a particular branch of the law.<ref>William H. Putman and Jennifer Albright. "II. Legal periodicals". ''Legal Research''. Third Edition. Cengage Learning. 2015. Pages [https://books.google.co.uk/books?id=tuXKAgAAQBAJ&pg=PA241#v=onepage&q&f=false 241] to 243 et seq. ''Legal Research, Analysis, and Writing''. Fourth Edition. 2018. Pages 193 and [https://books.google.co.uk/books?id=gEQqDwAAQBAJ&pg=PA194#v=onepage 194] et seq.</ref><ref>Linda L Edwards and J Stanley Edwards. "Legal Periodicals". Introduction to Paralegal Studies and the Law: A Practical Approach. West Legal Studies, Delmar, Thomson Learning. 2002. [https://books.google.co.uk/books?id=KAd01yB3uk4C&lpg=PA174&pg=PA174#v=onepage Page 174].</ref><ref>Martin A Frey and Sidney K Swinson. "E. Legal Periodicals". ''Introduction to Bankruptcy Law''. Delmar, Cengage Learning. Sixth Edition. 2012. [https://books.google.co.uk/books?id=Q5MsCQAAQBAJ&pg=PA31#v=onepage&q&f=false Page 31].</ref><ref>Carol M Bast and Margie A Hawkins. "Legal Periodicals". Foundations of Legal Research and Writing. 2012. [https://books.google.co.uk/books?id=pBT7CAAAQBAJ&pg=PA61#v=onepage Page 61] to 64.</ref><ref>A Yelin and H Viner Samborn. "H. Legal Periodicals". ''The Legal Research and Writing Handbook''. Eighth Edition. Wolters Kluwer. New York. 2018. [https://books.google.co.uk/books?id=auRLDwAAQBAJ&pg=PT262#v=onepage&q&f=false Page 262] to 265 et seq.</ref><ref>(2000) 88 Illinois Bar Journal 49 [https://books.google.co.uk/books?id=DnYvAQAAIAAJ Google Books]</ref><ref>Ronald W Tank. Legal Aspects of Geology. Plenum Press. New York. 1983. Pages [https://books.google.co.uk/books?id=xbXdBgAAQBAJ&pg=PT602#v=onepage 602] and 603.</ref>
The obituaries and profiles in legal periodicals may be useful to historians and biographers.<ref>Patrick Polden, "Judging Judges: The Reputations of Nineteenth-Century Judges and their Sources", in Anthony Musson and Chantal Stebbings (eds), ''Making Legal History: Approaches and Methodologies'', Cambridge University Press, 2012, Pages [https://books.google.co.uk/books?id=czCHiu1Jqw8C&pg=PA60#v=onepage&q&f=false 60] and 61.</ref><ref>Guy Holborn. Sources of Biographical Information on Past Lawyers. British and Irish Association of Law Librarians. 1999. Page 14. See also passim. [https://books.google.co.uk/books?id=Hl5HAQAAIAAJ Google Books]</ref> Book reviews in legal periodicals may be useful to librarians.<ref>Deborah S Panella. "Book Reviews in Law Reviews". Basics of Law Librarianship. The Haworth Press. 1991. Routledge. 2011. [https://books.google.co.uk/books?id=zP4Su6klaKUC&pg=PA21#v=onepage&q&f=false Page 21].</ref> There is a Book Review Index in the Index to Legal Periodicals.<ref>James R Acker and Richard Irving. Basic Legal Research for Criminal Justice and the Social Sciences. Aspen Publishers. Gaithersburg, Maryland. 1998. [https://books.google.co.uk/books?id=pYovmsHGTcQC&pg=PA94#v=onepage Page 94].</ref>
